    "differentiation_vs_east_hydrangea_sister": "Same 'hydrangea festival' product family, but **southwest garden-plus-geology emphasis**: 3 garden anchors (Hallim + Camellia Hill + Osulloc tea-fields) + 1 compound geology stop (Jusangjeolli+Cheonjeyeon) + 1 west-coast beach (Hyeopjae). The east sister covers **Hamdeok beach + Seongeup Joseon heritage + triple-ユネスコ Seongsan + Ilchul Land + Hueree** — a more ユネスコ-and-heritage-coded, higher-climb route. Booking matrix: guests with strong wedding-photo or hydrangea-tunnel interest + lower mobility tolerance + multi-garden preference should book southwest; guests with strong ユネスコ + Joseon heritage interest + willing to climb Seongsan should book east. **Both routes share Camellia Hill peak alignment in mid-June**, so the operator can offer parallel departures for both routes simultaneously during peak hydrangea weeks.",
